      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DR. BENEDICT (1) was out of in the placings when fourth last time but prior to that ran a quick 24.40 win over 435m at this track. Can measure up on top win two back. GAS AND DUST (4) caught the eye when clocking an exceptional 24.26 over 435m at this track. Harder here but will be in this for a long way. DR. PATRICK (2) failed to come into contention last start after being shuffled back early at Traralgon, but prior to that won by 1.3 lengths at this track (24.66) beating HAMMER ROSE in a Grade 5 H on April 19. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from four attempts. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. DR. BOBBY (3) has been in the placings at his last two runs, most recently when third (24.29) in a Grade 5 over 425m at Traralgon.",
